Hi! I flew today.
first complaint: we need pretty flight logs. Black is boring, pink isn't even pink, it's salmon.
I've wanted to fly since I was little.
And I did it today... today, I flew an airplane. I still can't believe it.
FlightAware data.
I'll try to do it next Saturday as well. The weather isn't great right now, but it's only Monday.
Difficulties are already starting to appear. I'm likely to have A LOT of trouble getting a medical certificate, due to the FAA's stance on certain medications.
Not impossible, but it will take ENORMOUS amounts of time and require a lot more work.
Even though it's discouraging, it's just another problem to solve, and for now, it seems *completely* manageable. It's just that it will take a lot of time and money.
In case you're interested in the challenge ahead of me.
The FAA is not a fan of ADHD. It does not issue a medical certificate if one is on treatment for it.
https://youtu.be/W5JSfq6LLAU?si=xIxPaY8ayqqNSj4c
If ever I get the chance to have a personalized registration number, it will DEFINITELY be a variation of N1337_, with _ corresponding to any available final alphabetical character.
Of course, the sun will shine while I'm gone, lol. What a fool.
I need to go flying again. And the weather isn't helping.
Welcome to the world of general aviation 😜
I get the impression that aviation tends to follow a rather conservative path if we look at the ads YouTube has decided I should see, the videos recommended to me, and the comments I can read.
